Delegates to the American Pork Congresswill decide whether or not they want mandatory productioncontrols when they vote on the official pork producer policywednesday, the National Pork Producers Council said.    The American Pork Congress, APC, delegates, listened toboth sides of the question when former Iowa Congressman BerkleyBedell and Bill Lesher, USDA Assistant Secretary for Economicsfor the years 1981 to 1985 debated at the convention inIndianapolis. Reuter&#3;